2164.subject: MLML
2164.descrlong: MLML 143:Chem Oceanograph-  An introduction to the theoretical and practical aspects of the chemistry of the oceans including major salts, dissolved gases, nutrient ions, carbonate system, transient tracers, and shipboard sampling techniques. Offered through Moss Landing Marine Laboratories (MLML); contact SEP program office for MLML registration procedures. (Offered spring semester.)
